%multipage fixture - pins PS/JSON pagination parity.
%Nine identical sections auto-paginate (no explicit page breaks anywhere,
%so the page boundary is decided solely by more()). Section heights are
%tuned so the last section that just fits under PS's top-of-page origin is
%exactly the one an over-large JSON budget would pull up a page.
%With the pre-fix JSON origin (full paper height, no top-margin deduction)
%JSON gets ~0.58in more budget per page and over-fills to 2 pages; the PS
%pipeline paginates to 3. Post-fix, json_print starts each page at the
%ps_top_of_page equivalent, so both pipelines produce 3 pages.

{Multipage pagination fixture}

{Section}

